.SH NAME
dotty-dotfiles - Operate on the dotfiles repository dotty init generated.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty dotfiles [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Link, inspect, and recover the dotfiles repository created by dotty init —
or any repository with the same layout: a home/ tree of $HOME-relative
entries plus profiles/ directories whose profile.json records the choices
that built them.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for dotfiles

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	dotfiles repository (default: found via $REPOS_DIR)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty dotfiles status
  dotty dotfiles link --on-conflict=backup
  dotty dotfiles restore
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty(1)\fP, \fBdotty-dotfiles-link(1)\fP, \fBdotty-dotfiles-restore(1)\fP, \fBdotty-dotfiles-status(1)\fP
